description.plain:
Khadimou Rassoul Cheikh Fall (b. September 10, 1998), known by the stage name Sheck Wes, is a rapper and model from Harlem, New York. He is of Senegalese descent.

The song primarily responsible for Sheck’s rise to fame is “Mo Bamba,” which was released on June 16, 2017.

On February 1, 2018, Sheck Wes announced that he had signed to Interscope Records through a joint venture between Kanye West’s G.O.O.D. Music and Travis Scott’s Cactus Jack Records. https://twitter.com/sheckwes/status/959193336455327745

On August 3, 2018, Sheck appeared on Travis’ third studio album, ASTROWORLD, rapping the chorus on the track, “NO BYSTANDERS.”

Sheck released his debut studio album, MUDBOY, on October 5, 2018.

Sheck Wes is also a part of the group, JACKBOYS, which is composed of the signees of Cactus Jack Records. The group released their self-titled debut on December 27, 2019.

description.plain: “Mo Bamba” is a track named after Orlando Magic and former Texas Longhorn center Mohamed Bamba. He grew up playing basketball with Sheck and in this song, Sheck compares his experience as an up-and-coming rapper being targeted by labels with Bamba’s experience as a high school recruit being hassled by colleges.

songs.title: Chippi Chippi

description.plain:
“Chippi Chippi” is the fourth released single from Sheck Wes' upcoming album, MUDBOY.

With dark production courtesy of producer Redda, Sheck gives listeners a glimpse into his celebrity-lifestyle with this loosely—and almost freely—rapped track. Wes described the song as “leaving a place in a state of anger, with intentions to get high” and further explained the meaning of “chippi chippi” on Instagram:

When you mad or anxious to leave somewhere to smoke, derived from the language of @wigglehot, LUSTLANGUAGE curated by Sheckwes.

The official music video for the song was released August 28, 2018, on Sheck’s Youtube channel.

“Live Sheck Wes” (originally “Live SheckWes Die SheckWes”) is the second single from MUDBOY.

‘Live Sheck Wes’ is a song about roaches in the crib. I’m in the projects right now and I got roaches in the kitchen, but I don’t care about that shit. This is me, why should I hate it?
